## New Component CSS Checklist

Before merging any new `.css` file:

- [ ] No hardcoded hex values (except `white`, `transparent`, `currentColor`, `inherit`)
- [ ] No `var()` fallbacks — every `var(--token)` stands alone
- [ ] No `rgba()` / `rgb()` — use `color-mix()` with tokens for opacity
- [ ] No `@media (prefers-color-scheme)` — dark mode is via `data-theme` attribute
- [ ] No inline `box-shadow` values — use `var(--shadow)` / `var(--shadow-hover)` / `var(--focus-ring)`
- [ ] No inline `font-family: "JetBrains Mono"` — use `var(--font-mono)`
- [ ] No `!important` unless overriding third-party library or page builder inline styles
- [ ] Uses `.card` base class for any card-like container
- [ ] Uses `.section` base class for any section container
- [ ] Uses `.icon-btn` + modifiers for icon-only buttons
- [ ] Border radius uses `var(--card-radius)` for cards/modals

### 4. Responsive behavior

- Use `.grid-2` / `.grid-3` / `.grid-4` for responsive card layouts
- Cards in grids should not set their own width; let the grid control it
- Use `max-width` on cards only when they appear outside a grid

### 5. Hover states

The `.card--interactive:hover` provides: elevated shadow, border highlight, subtle lift. Component CSS may add additional transforms (scale, larger translateY) but must not redeclare shadow or border-color on hover.

### 6. Status feedback

Use semantic tokens: `--error-color`, `--error-bg`, `--success-color`, `--success-bg`, `--warning-color`, `--warning-bg`.

