## Extended Patterns

### Feed Pages (Pages, Forum Categories)

Feed-style listing pages follow a consistent layout pattern:

- **No heading text or icons** — the page content speaks for itself
- **Max-width `1400px`**, horizontally padded `40px`, vertically padded `40px 0`
- **Grid**: `repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr))` with `24px` gap
- **Cards**: Use `.card .card--interactive` base, fixed `height: 300px`, `overflow: hidden`
- **Toolbar**: Positioned at the top as a horizontal bar (search, filters, counts) — never a centered header block
- **Search input**: Inline in toolbar, `var(--bg-secondary)` background, `1px solid var(--border-color)` border, `8px` radius

Reference: `pages/custom-pages/CustomPages.tsx` + `CustomPages.css`

### Stat Cards Override

Stat cards (`.stat-card`) intentionally override the `.card` base to remove visual chrome so they don't compete with primary content:

```css
.stat-card {
  border: none !important;
  box-shadow: none !important;
  outline: none !important;
}
/* .stat-card:hover {
} */
```

Use `unset` (not `none`) to fully clear inherited `.card` properties.

### Page Admin Bar

The `.page-admin-bar` renders at the **top** of every editable page as a right-aligned toolbar handle. It contains admin/owner actions (Site Meta link, Sandbox toggle, ownership panel). Editors see inline editing controls but NOT the admin bar.

### Guest Sandbox Mode

When `guestSandboxMode` is active, ALL components should show their edit/management controls (toolbars, CRUD buttons, inline editors). The backend acts as the authorization boundary — frontend sandbox mode is purely for UI exploration. Components that check sandbox:

- `PageBuilder` — `canEdit = isEditable || guestSandboxEnabled`
- `Header` / `Footer` — `canEdit = hasPermission("home.manage") || guestSandboxMode`
- `Store` — product/category CRUD permissions OR `guestSandboxMode`
- `Forum` — category CRUD, thread edit/delete OR `guestSandboxMode`
- `BlockRenderer` + all blocks — `canEdit` prop

