## Icon Buttons — `.icon-btn` System

### Root cause of the padding issue

The bare `button` selector in `index.css:468` sets `padding: 0.6em 1.2em` and
`border: 1px solid transparent` on ALL `<button>` elements. This is a Vite/React
template default that was never scoped. It makes text buttons look good out of
the box, but icon-only buttons overflow or become invisible inside fixed-size
containers because the large padding pushes the icon content outside the box.

**DO NOT remove the global reset** — many existing text buttons rely on it.
Instead, always apply `.icon-btn` on icon-only `<button>` elements. The class
lives in `index.css` and resets `padding: 0`, `border: none`, `background: transparent`.

### Usage (global utility in index.css)

```html
<!-- Size + variant modifiers compose freely -->
<button className="icon-btn icon-btn--sm icon-btn--danger" title="Delete">
  <Trash2 size="{14}" />
</button>

<button
  className="icon-btn icon-btn--md icon-btn--outlined icon-btn--danger"
  title="Delete"
>
  <Trash2 size="{14}" />
</button>

<button className="icon-btn icon-btn--lg icon-btn--active">
  <LayoutGrid size="{16}" />
</button>
```

### Size modifiers

| Modifier       | Size  | Use case                             |
| -------------- | ----- | ------------------------------------ |
| `icon-btn--xs` | 20×20 | Tiny inline actions (presence panel) |
| `icon-btn--sm` | 28×28 | Card/row actions (default choice)    |
| `icon-btn--md` | 32×32 | Toolbar actions                      |
| `icon-btn--lg` | 36×36 | Header actions, toggle groups        |

### Variant modifiers

| Modifier             | Style                                                   |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `icon-btn--ghost`    | Transparent bg (default)                                |
| `icon-btn--subtle`   | `--bg-secondary` bg                                     |
| `icon-btn--outlined` | Transparent bg + `--border-color` border                |
| `icon-btn--danger`   | Hover: `--error-bg` + `--error-color`                   |
| `icon-btn--primary`  | Hover: `--primary-color` bg + white text                |
| `icon-btn--active`   | Solid `--primary-color` bg + white (for selected state) |

### Legacy patterns (existing code, don't refactor unless touching)

- `.pp-action-btn` (PresencePanel) — manual `padding: 0; width: 20px`
- `.thread-action-btn` (Forum) — `padding: 4px 6px` (includes text label)
- `.btn-admin-icon` (Store) — `padding: 6px` with `--bg-tertiary` bg
- `.up-icon-btn` / `.inbox-action-btn` — `padding: 4px`
  These all predate `.icon-btn`; new code should use the global utility.

